webResources.textAttributionSnippet: (en) Sturefors Castle is beautifully situated on Lake Erlågen. Castles were completed around 1710. The village lord was Karl XII’s powerful head of the cabinet Count Carl Piper and, in order to meet his wishes, he knocked the extremely reputable architect Nicodemus Tessin d. y. for the mission - https://www.europeana.eu/item/73/S_OM_photo_OMFB000637.
